CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 20, 1962, pg. 17, reads: "King and Queen - Reigning in splendid royalty is the seated couple. Chairman Evelyn Burks (standing) of Iron City 17 crowned Dt. Alvinus Woods as queen and Curtis Newring as king, at the Cap and Gown Ball sponsored recently by the education committee of Bon Ami Temple 49, IBPOE of W. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Evelyn Burks placing snowflake patterned crown on "queen" of Iron City Elks Alvinus Woods, with "king" Curtis Newring on left, at Cap and Gown Ball, another version
